I'm not an Uzi fan myself-- listened to XO Tour life cuz who hasn't and enjoyed most of his features in other songs so when my friends notified me that he dropping this a few days ago, I thought "ay, here's my chance to see what he's about"

And yeah, I was kinda disappointed
My friends, who are long fans of Uzi's work are enjoying the album, and there are some songs like Silly Watch, Baby Pluto, P2 and the bonus tracks that I can find something in to appreciate so I'm happy for em

I'm still gonna keep listening and stuff to see if there's anything more to appreciate in it, but I might just look into his previous works incase I find anything on the level of XO tour life and the features I always enjoy

snippet.textDisplay: All I'm saying is the more you listen to Uzi, the more you like him, and this album was an exact replica of that. When i first listened, i only liked a few songs, but now after listening to it again, giving it another chance, im addicted. Im not saying the album was bad, and neither am I saying Uzi is, as I love his music and unequity so much its hard to put into words. What I am saying, however, is that Uzi isnt overhyped at all, and he is largelty influential. His music is of high quality 9 times out of 10, with that 1 time just not being it for me, but is easily it for someone else. This album wasnt the strongest hes released (my opinion LUV is rage 2 was) but it is still incredible to most, and well worth the near 3 year wait, especially due to a deluxe being dropped tonight of me writing this. This man, right here, on your screen, whos video you are watching, has valid opinions no matter what. His opinions may not match to yours, but music is constantly changing, and what you may adore, another might hate. Dont let someone change your perspective of something, as only you can control who and what you love
